WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:07.000
Sleep has gone from being a sleepy topic to one that is now heavily studied by top-tier researchers.

00:07.000 --> 00:12.000
While there is still some mystery surrounding why humans need so much sleep,

00:12.000 --> 00:16.000
there really is no mystery about how essential it is to get enough.

00:16.000 --> 00:21.000
Yet, when I talk with my clients and ask them how they're sleeping,

00:21.000 --> 00:26.000
about half of the time I'm met with, I roll size and visible frustration.

00:26.000 --> 00:29.000
Many people simply aren't sleeping well.

00:30.000 --> 00:35.000
Hi, I'm Melanie Luther, I'm a certified nutrition specialist and a licensed dietitian nutritionist.

00:35.000 --> 00:42.000
Level up your sleep is a thoughtfully designed nutritional supplement that may help support better sleep.

00:42.000 --> 00:50.000
It contains magnesium by glycinate, a highly bio-available, well absorbed form of this essential mineral.

00:50.000 --> 00:56.000
Research suggests that magnesium by glycinate may modestly improve sleep quality

00:56.000 --> 00:59.000
and support both falling asleep and staying asleep.

00:59.000 --> 01:06.000
Without adequate magnesium, it's incredibly difficult for the nervous system to relax and turn off at night.

01:06.000 --> 01:12.000
L-fianian is a non-essential amino acid that helps to ease the mind.

01:12.000 --> 01:18.000
It supports the transition from the active brain wave states of alertness and problem solving

01:18.000 --> 01:23.000
into the alpha state associated with relaxation and meditation.

01:23.000 --> 01:26.000
A state much more conducive for sleeping.

01:26.000 --> 01:30.000
Many people find it helps you quiet that mental chatter that seems to get louder

01:30.000 --> 01:33.000
the moment our heads hit the pillow.

01:33.000 --> 01:37.000
Ashragand is another valuable addition to this formula.

01:37.000 --> 01:43.000
A meta-analysis of five randomized controlled trials involving over 400 participants

01:43.000 --> 01:49.000
found a small but significant improvement in overall sleep with the greatest benefit seen

01:49.000 --> 01:52.000
in individuals experiencing insomnia.

01:52.000 --> 01:58.000
Its angelitic properties, meaning it's ability to calm feelings of anxiety, may also

01:58.000 --> 02:02.000
support sleep in those experiencing chronic stress.

02:02.000 --> 02:05.000
Last but not least is Vitamin B6.

02:05.000 --> 02:11.000
This essential B vitamin is required for the production of key sleep-related neurotransmitters,

02:11.000 --> 02:15.000
including melatonin, GABA, serotonin and dopamine.

02:15.000 --> 02:20.000
It's also important to know that regular alcohol consumption and high caffeine intake

02:20.000 --> 02:26.000
can negatively impact vitamin B6 status which may contribute to difficulty falling or staying

02:26.000 --> 02:27.000
asleep.

02:27.000 --> 02:31.500
Additionally, I think it's important to know that supplementing with Vitamin B6 may increase

02:31.500 --> 02:34.000
dream vividness and recall.

02:34.000 --> 02:34.500
Thank you so much.
